{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772634132,"nonce":"aJUCmOGovtYn/WiLHJrNKu0OjXI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vvuuZ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/343","origin":"github"},"title":"Add triage-copilot skill for evaluating Copilot review feedback","message":"## Summary\n\nAdd a `triage-copilot` skill that evaluates new GitHub Copilot review comments on a PR against the local worktree code, workspace principles, and ADRs. Produces a classified plan for the user to approve — does not auto-fix.\n\n## Motivation\n\nReviewing Copilot feedback is a frequent manual task: open the PR, read each comment, decide if it's valid or a false positive, then plan fixes. This skill automates the triage and planning steps.\n\n## Proposed Flow\n\n```\n/triage-copilot \u003cPR-number\u003e\n```\n\n1. **Confirm worktree**: Verify the current worktree branch matches the PR's head branch\n2. **Sync**: `git pull` to ensure local matches remote\n3. **Get HEAD timestamp**: Use the timestamp of the most recent commit as the cutoff\n4. **Fetch comments**: `gh api` to get Copilot review comments submitted after `HEAD`'s timestamp\n5. **Evaluate locally**: For each comment, read the local file at the referenced path/line. Assess validity against the actual code, principles, and ADRs\n6. **Classify and present plan**: Structured output in conversation — valid issues with fix descriptions, false positives with reasoning\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n- **Local evaluation**: Read files from the worktree, not via `git show` or remote fetches. Avoids permission prompts and is faster.\n- **\"Since last commit\" filter**: Only consider comments newer than `HEAD`. If you've already committed a fix, the comment is filtered out — simple and effective.\n- **Plan only, no auto-fix**: The skill stops at presenting a classified plan. Fixes are left to the normal workflow. Comment types vary too much (one-line fixes vs architectural changes) for batch automation.\n- **In-conversation output**: Like `review-pr`, output stays in the conversation. No files written, no comments posted.\n\n## Skill Lifecycle Position\n\nUtility skill — invoked after Copilot reviews a PR, before implementing fixes. Complements `review-pr` (which does a governance review) by triaging external review feedback.\n\n## References\n\n- `review-pr` skill — similar output pattern\n- `onboard-project` skill — similar triage-then-act pattern (but this skill stops at triage)\n- `pr_status.sh` — could surface PRs with unresolved Copilot comments to feed into this skill\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}